===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈte.pɪd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-tepid.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
In the Roman baths, there was a room called the ''[[tepidarium]]'', or "Warm Room", so tepid is probably derived from this

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# [[lukewarm|Lukewarm]].
#: ''a '''tepid''' cup of water''
# [[uninterested|Uninterested]]; exhibiting little passion or eagerness.
#: ''as in a '''tepid''' response to the proposal''

